The paper proposes a new framework for semi-supervised learning on graph-structured data, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning and artificial intelligence fields. The paper also mentions the use of scalable variational inference techniques, which suggests a focus on computational methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves graph theory and network science, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
